results.name: Smallest k>=1 such that A067128(n+k) - A067128(n) is in A067128 or a(n)=0 if there is no such k.
comment: For n=151, the required k, if it exists, should be >9800. So one can conjecture that a(151) is the first zero term.
results.author: _Vladimir Shevelev_ and _Peter J. C. Moses_, May 09 2016
